SIMPLE: glebe
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Glebe
<hw>Glebe</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>gl⟦egrave⟧be</ets>, L. <ets>gleba</ets>, <ets>glaeba</ets>, clod,
land, soil.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A lump; a clod.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Turf; soil; ground; sod.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Fertile of corn the <qex>glebe</qex>, of oil, and wine.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Eccl. Law)</fld> <def>The land belonging, or
yielding revenue, to a parish church or ecclesiastical
benefice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glebeless</ent>⟦br⟧
